{"body": "@steveklabnik yes. Draper uses method_missing and respond_to? to delegate to the model.\n\nThe issue I ran into was triggered by calling a method on the wrapped model within a decorator, which internally uses associations (has_one in my case). When doing so, it spits out an \"undefined method `locked' for #<Class:0x007f82fb067068>\", like this: https://gist.github.com/7498247d20ecd191d77e.\n\nI spent a bunch of time chasing the cause, and finally ended up renaming my \"locked\" named scope to something else.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7731616", "created_at": "2012-08-14T16:36:04Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6985#issuecomment-7731616", "updated_at": "2012-08-14T16:36:04Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6985, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/ihoka", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/b24f89b9d2b99c1fb48c7ab5fff9ab48?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F14b9130e6dbe8185cb68fa211921a335.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/received_events", "gravatar_id": "b24f89b9d2b99c1fb48c7ab5fff9ab48", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "ihoka", "type": "User", "id": 30113, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ihoka/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380133bd3543c15100c0e4"}, "id": 7731616, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6985"}
